2 pipe operator

Ctrl+Shift+M

#mpg ggplot()
mpg %>% ggplot(aes(displ, hwy,color = class)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_wrap(~drv)

#  mpg  2008  ggplot 
#  "displ"  x "hwy"  y "class" "drv" 
mpg %>% 
  filter(year==2008) %>% # 
  ggplot(aes(displ, hwy,color = class)) + # 
  geom_point() + # 
  facet_wrap(~drv) # 

#  mpg  "compact"  "suv"  ggplot 
#  "displ"  x "hwy"  y "class" "drv" 
mpg %>% 
  filter(class == "compact" | class == "suv") %>% # 
  ggplot(aes(displ, hwy,color = class)) + # 
  geom_point() + # 
  facet_wrap(~drv) #

#  mpg  ggplot()  "manufacturer"  x 
#  geom_bar() 
# col 5fill 5
mpg %>% 
  ggplot(aes(manufacturer)) + 
  geom_bar(col = 5, fill = 5)

3.2 

#  ggplot()  mpg  "manufacturer"  x  fct_infreq() 
#  geom_bar() 
# col 6fill 6
#  guides()  x 
# guide_axis()  angle 
mpg %>% ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(manufacturer))) + 
  geom_bar(col = 6, fill = 6)+
  guides(x = guide_axis(angle = 90))+
  labs(title = "Pareto Diagram", x = "Manufacturer")

#geom_text
mpg %>%     #mpgggplot
  ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(manufacturer))) + #x
  geom_bar(col = 5, fill = 5)+            # 
  geom_text(stat = "count",               # 
            aes(label = after_stat(count)), # 
            vjust = -0.5)+     # 0.5
  guides(x = guide_axis(angle = 45))+
  labs(title = "Pareto Diagram", x = "Manufacturer")

3.3 

# position = "dodge"  side by side bar plot 
mpg %>%
  filter(manufacturer == "ford" | manufacturer == "toyota") %>%  #  "ford"  "toyota" 
  ggplot(aes(manufacturer, fill = class)) +  #  ggplot2  x 
  geom_bar(position = "dodge", alpha = 0.5) +  # position = "dodge" alpha = 0.5  0.5
  theme_bw() +  # 
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # 
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +  # 
  labs(title = "Class and Manufacturer", x = "manufacturer", y = "Number")  # x  y

3.4 

#position = "fill" 
mpg %>%
  filter(manufacturer == "ford" | manufacturer == "toyota") %>%  #  "ford"  "toyota" 
  ggplot(aes(manufacturer, fill = class)) +  #  ggplot2  x 
  geom_bar(position = "fill", alpha = 0.5) +  # position = "fill" alpha = 0.5  0.5
  theme_bw() +  # 
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # 
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +  # 
  labs(title = "Class and Manufacturer", x = "manufacturer", y = "Number")  # x  y

4.2 

mpg %>% 
  ggplot(aes(cty))+
  geom_histogram(col = 1, fill = 5, binwidth = 2)+
  stat_bin(aes(label = after_stat(count)), binwidth = 2, 
           geom = "text",vjust = -0.5)+
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,50), breaks = seq(0,50,5))+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(9,35,2))

#
mpg %>% 
  ggplot(aes(cty))+
  geom_histogram(aes(fill = ..count..), col = 1, binwidth = 2)+
  stat_bin(aes(label = ..count..), binwidth = 2, 
           geom = "text",vjust = -0.5)+
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,50), breaks = seq(0,50,5))+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(9,35,2))+
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "cyan3", high = "cyan")

#mpgdrive
#recode
mpg <- mpg %>% 
  mutate(drive = recode(drv,"f" ="Front Drive", "r" = "Rear Drive", 
                      "4" = "Four-Wheel Drive")) 

mpg %>% 
  ggplot(aes(cty, fill = drive))+
  geom_histogram()+
  facet_wrap(~drive, ncol = 1)        
`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

  geom_histogram()+

            hjust = 0.5,

  x = "city miles per gallon",
  y = "highway miles per gallon")

mpg %>% 
  ggplot(aes(cty,hwy,col = transmission,
             alpha=0.5))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = F)+
  facet_wrap(~transmission)+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
  panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  labs(title = "Fuel Economy in City & Highway",
  x = "city miles per gallon",
  y = "highway miles per gallon")
`geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

mpg %>% 
  ggplot(aes(cty,hwy,col = transmission,alpha=0.3))+
  geom_point(aes(size = cyl))+
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = F)+
  facet_wrap(~transmission)+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
  panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  labs(title = "Fuel Economy in City & Highway",
  x = "city miles per gallon",
  y = "highway miles per gallon")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 16),
        axis.text = element_text(color = "blue", size = 12),
        strip.text = element_text(color = "blue", size = 12))
